Marco Levorato 


Ph.D. Telecommunication Engineering
Research Interests: 
Machine Learning for SystemsSystems for Machine LearningDistributed and Edge computingVehicular autonomyHealthcare
Email: levorato@uci.edu


Education:
2010-2012 – Post Doctorate Scholar, Electrical Engineering, Stanford University and the University of Southern California, USA2009 – Ph.D. in Telecommunications Engineering, University of Padova, Italy2005 – M.E. in Telecommunication Engineering (summa cum laude), University of Ferrara, Italy2002 – B.E. inTelecommunication Engineering(summa cum laude), University of Ferrara, Italy

Awards and Honors
2022 – IEEE Senior Member2022 – Distinguished Member of the 2022 IEEE INFOCOM Technical Program Committee2019 – Dean’s Mid Career Research Award2016 – University of California Hellman Award2012 – Best paper award – IEEE Global Communications Conference (Globecom) 2012, Signal processing symposium2012 – Winner of the ACCESS Post Doctoral research fellowship at the ACCESS Linnaeus Center, Royal Institute of Technology (KTH), Sweden.2010 – Nominated for the Best Young Researcher Award, Dept. of Information Engineering, University of Padova, Italy.2009 – Nominated for the Best Young Researcher Award, Dept. of Information Engineering, University of Padova, Italy.
